1
00:00:24,149 --> 00:00:27,944
Did I ever get slapped!

2
00:00:28,194 --> 00:00:33,992
They caught me coming out of
Roman Holiday at a Left Bank cinema.

3
00:00:34,242 --> 00:00:39,414
Not only did I skip school,
but American movies were off-limits.

4
00:00:40,081 --> 00:00:45,462
Dad found them silly and Mom said
they weren't true to life.

5
00:00:45,712 --> 00:00:49,424
Okay, the poor get rich,
the rich have problems,

6
00:00:49,674 --> 00:00:52,969
immigrants are legalized, wars end,

7
00:00:53,219 --> 00:00:56,723
even the dead come back,
and whores marry millionaires.

8
00:00:56,973 --> 00:00:58,391
If only it could all be true!

9
00:01:01,144 --> 00:01:03,313
Andy Warhol said...
- Say, another American! -

10
00:01:06,358 --> 00:01:10,320
that everyone should be famous
for 15 minutes in his life.

11
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:14,240
always felt I had a right
to a whole day.

12
00:01:14,491 --> 00:01:18,953
A whole day when my life
would be like an American movie.

13
00:02:21,766 --> 00:02:24,227
Why are we landing in Paris?

14
00:02:34,487 --> 00:02:37,907
JET LAG

15
00:03:57,112 --> 00:03:59,364
I'm calling from Paris.

16
00:03:59,614 --> 00:04:02,283
Nothing, I'm not staying here.

17
00:04:02,534 --> 00:04:07,497
Besides, it's a madhouse as usual:
strikes, school vacation...

18
00:04:07,747 --> 00:04:11,251
I'm going to Munich,
but the weather's bad.

19
00:04:11,710 --> 00:04:15,422
No, it wasn't planned.
Nadia's grandmother died.

20
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:20,844
That's beside the point.
I was fond of her grandma.

21
00:04:35,483 --> 00:04:38,236
Departure times are undetermined.

22
00:04:41,322 --> 00:04:45,243
You must have some idea when.

23
00:04:45,618 --> 00:04:47,662
Not with the strike.

24
00:04:47,996 --> 00:04:51,291
- What strike?
- Public utilities,

25
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:54,627
now the air-traffic controllers.
It's vacation!

26
00:04:54,878 --> 00:04:58,381
French Rail is joining in.

27
00:04:58,631 --> 00:05:00,050
Aisle or window?

28
00:05:02,552 --> 00:05:05,388
The trains are on strike, too?

29
00:05:05,638 --> 00:05:07,057
No aisle seats.

30
00:05:08,558 --> 00:05:10,810
It's a disaster!

31
00:05:13,563 --> 00:05:17,275
- Or in the last row.
- A window's fine.

32
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:19,569
The trains, you sure?

33
00:05:22,864 --> 00:05:26,242
Your ticket and baggage check.

34
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:45,845
Hang on.

35
00:05:54,521 --> 00:05:55,855
You still there?

36
00:05:56,106 --> 00:06:02,320
C'mon, it's not that far!
I'll pay your cab fare to mother's.

37
00:06:02,696 --> 00:06:06,282
Have the taxi wait, go upstairs.

38
00:06:06,533 --> 00:06:09,202
The letter's on the nightstand.

39
00:06:09,869 --> 00:06:14,624
By the phone,
an envelope marked Sergio.

40
00:06:14,874 --> 00:06:17,877
Take it and run.

41
00:06:18,336 --> 00:06:20,380
You have the door code?

42
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:23,091
Write it down:

43
00:06:23,341 --> 00:06:26,428
36 B 48. Can you hear me?

44
00:06:29,431 --> 00:06:31,141
No, B as in...

45
00:06:37,105 --> 00:06:39,149
Oh, shit!

46
00:06:41,609 --> 00:06:46,656
This can't be happening.

47
00:07:05,175 --> 00:07:07,927
Be tough.
Gloria McKornick will be there.

48
00:07:08,178 --> 00:07:12,098
No, the pain-in-the-ass
"food engineer."

49
00:07:12,349 --> 00:07:15,852
The one who killed
our Shepherd's Pie...

50
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:20,857
She's a menace.
All she likes is Chicken Bechamel.

51
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:24,611
And Bruno,
it's uptown this time.

52
00:07:24,861 --> 00:07:27,113
On their turf, not ours.

53
00:07:34,788 --> 00:07:38,500
Would you mind?
Just for a local call.

54
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:42,671
I lost mine
and the phone booths are all...

55
00:07:42,921 --> 00:07:45,882
It's really urgent.
You don't mind?

56
00:07:47,092 --> 00:07:49,552
Write this down: 36 B 48.

57
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:52,681
Right, B as in Bernard.

58
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:56,643
Sure, she'll give them to you.

59
00:07:56,893 --> 00:08:00,814
No, you know how she is.
I'm not up to calling her now.

60
00:08:02,524 --> 00:08:08,279
Whatever! That you're borrowing
a dress, my leg waxer...

61
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:13,743
Do it now. Promise! With the strike
he'll come home and find the letter.

62
00:08:14,202 --> 00:08:18,331
I let it all out. I say goodbye...

63
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:21,668
Stop it! I'm with...

64
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:26,464
I'm not scared, but if he shows up
here, I'm afraid I might...

65
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:30,635
I'm stuck, everything's held up.

66
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:35,432
There are no planes taking off.
Hurry!

67
00:08:57,912 --> 00:09:01,416
There's coffee. Care for a coffee?

68
00:09:03,752 --> 00:09:06,004
Mind if I have a coffee?

69
00:09:06,254 --> 00:09:09,758
- My cell phone?
- Sorry.

70
00:09:10,008 --> 00:09:13,303
Not even a glass of water?

71
00:10:01,226 --> 00:10:04,312
Are you Rose? It's for you.

72
00:10:04,562 --> 00:10:06,815
Sorry,
the number must've registered.

73
00:10:07,065 --> 00:10:09,859
I'll just be a minute.

74
00:10:11,569 --> 00:10:12,570
Mom?

75
00:10:14,781 --> 00:10:18,910
How'd you get the number?
She shouldn't have.

76
00:10:19,369 --> 00:10:23,498
I'm not at the beauty parlor today.
I'll explain later.

77
00:10:26,334 --> 00:10:28,712
You didn't do that?!

78
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:31,006
How many did you take?

79
00:10:31,256 --> 00:10:34,759
How many are left? The box was full?

80
00:10:37,095 --> 00:10:39,973
Then it's not too serious.

81
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:45,812
No, nothing else! Not even aspirin.
You'll sleep tonight.

82
00:10:50,442 --> 00:10:53,111
I can't right now.

83
00:10:54,195 --> 00:10:59,159
I can't come over now.
Not today, Mom.

84
00:10:59,868 --> 00:11:02,912
No little massage today.

85
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:08,209
Sure, I love you.

86
00:11:10,545 --> 00:11:13,340
Give my key to Sabine.

87
00:11:16,426 --> 00:11:17,844
Of course

88
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:24,726
I'm still your little girl.
Wherever I am, wherever you are.

89
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:31,191
Of course. Lots of love...

90
00:12:22,951 --> 00:12:25,412
That was really sweet of you.

91
00:12:25,662 --> 00:12:26,955
Are you okay?

92
00:12:27,205 --> 00:12:28,957
What's wrong?

93
00:12:32,335 --> 00:12:35,005
In my bag. There.

94
00:12:35,255 --> 00:12:38,758
The pills in my bag.

95
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:42,721
You'll be all right.

96
00:12:50,687 --> 00:12:52,731
- A problem?
- I don't know.

97
00:12:54,649 --> 00:12:56,484
Sit down.

98
00:12:57,861 --> 00:12:59,821
I'll call a doctor.

99
00:13:00,488 --> 00:13:04,200
I'll massage you, it'll help.
Just relax.

100
00:13:04,534 --> 00:13:06,494
Don't touch me.

101
00:13:07,787 --> 00:13:10,665
- You taking a plane?
- I hope so.

102
00:13:12,584 --> 00:13:14,836
Stop by the drugstore.

103
00:13:15,086 --> 00:13:16,713
It's a sedative.

104
00:13:16,963 --> 00:13:19,215
Only if the symptoms recur.

105
00:13:19,466 --> 00:13:21,509
You mean if my heart beats fast?

106
00:13:21,760 --> 00:13:24,637
- Not fast, hard.
- There a difference?

107
00:13:24,888 --> 00:13:27,557
Fast is here. Hard is here.

108
00:13:27,807 --> 00:13:30,268
Think I enjoy fainting?

109
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:32,979
Relax. There's no physical disorder.

110
00:13:33,229 --> 00:13:37,108
If you feel faint, put your feet up.

111
00:13:47,744 --> 00:13:50,622
- Feeling better?
- Fine, just fine.

112
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,461
- What'd he say?
- Nothing.

113
00:13:57,128 --> 00:13:59,589
I wanted to return your...

114
00:14:01,925 --> 00:14:03,551
If I can do anything...

115
00:14:03,802 --> 00:14:06,054
Everything's fine, thanks.

116
00:14:07,597 --> 00:14:11,685
- Goodbye.
- I wanted to tell you...

117
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:17,524
Go easy on those pills.
It's habit-forming and...

118
00:14:18,066 --> 00:14:21,986
And... while you were...

119
00:14:23,822 --> 00:14:26,908
No, nothing.

120
00:14:27,492 --> 00:14:29,285
Goodbye.

121
00:14:53,018 --> 00:14:54,352
Nadia!

122
00:14:57,022 --> 00:14:58,606
What message?

123
00:15:00,859 --> 00:15:04,154
No, I didn't get any messages.

124
00:15:08,366 --> 00:15:11,870
Hang on, someone's trying to call.

125
00:15:15,498 --> 00:15:17,167
Sabine who?

126
00:15:17,792 --> 00:15:19,586
Rose who?

127
00:15:21,171 --> 00:15:24,382
No, Rose isn't here!

128
00:15:24,966 --> 00:15:28,345
I don't know. How should l?

129
00:15:28,678 --> 00:15:30,138
What?

130
00:15:30,347 --> 00:15:32,015
Repeat that.

131
00:15:32,265 --> 00:15:35,101
Sergio? Who's Sergio?

132
00:15:40,690 --> 00:15:44,611
I've had enough. I can't help you.
I'm taking a plane.

133
00:15:44,861 --> 00:15:46,905
I'm sorry, but...

134
00:15:47,364 --> 00:15:50,241
That's right, goodbye, ma'am.

135
00:16:49,134 --> 00:16:53,138
- It's tiring. I'm stressed out.
- Are you?

136
00:16:53,388 --> 00:16:54,723
You have to understand me.

137
00:16:54,973 --> 00:16:57,434
We'll take a vacation.

138
00:16:57,767 --> 00:17:00,437
We need a month off together.

139
00:17:01,187 --> 00:17:04,399
Wherever you want.
You decide where.

140
00:17:05,108 --> 00:17:06,276
I put in for vacation.

141
00:17:09,279 --> 00:17:14,200
It's just to say, Sergio's
on his way. Apparently in a rage,

142
00:17:14,576 --> 00:17:16,703
out of control.

143
00:17:16,953 --> 00:17:19,622
Your friend said to warn you.
Sabine...

144
00:17:19,873 --> 00:17:21,291
That her name?

145
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:25,462
I think she ran into him
at your place.

146
00:17:27,255 --> 00:17:29,424
She says he's dangerous.

147
00:17:35,013 --> 00:17:36,431
Meet Sergio.

148
00:17:46,483 --> 00:17:48,735
I'm sorry, I don't...

149
00:17:50,028 --> 00:17:52,280
Felix. Felix Doumergue.

150
00:17:56,076 --> 00:17:59,996
This'll teach me a lesson.

151
00:18:00,246 --> 00:18:03,750
- Sorry, that was dumb of me.
- Who's he?

152
00:18:04,918 --> 00:18:07,712
Nobody. Tell him.

153
00:18:08,171 --> 00:18:10,215
We're total strangers.

154
00:18:11,925 --> 00:18:13,968
Sit down, have a drink.

155
00:18:18,264 --> 00:18:19,808
Sit down!

156
00:18:32,362 --> 00:18:33,154
What'll it be?

157
00:18:34,656 --> 00:18:36,282
Lemon soda.

158
00:18:41,538 --> 00:18:43,373
- Let me explain...
- Don't bother.

159
00:18:43,623 --> 00:18:45,375
Let him!

160
00:18:46,751 --> 00:18:48,837
I have a flight, sorry.

161
00:18:52,298 --> 00:18:54,134
I'll explain, then.

162
00:19:00,223 --> 00:19:03,309
See this woman? Look at her.

163
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:11,234
At first glance she's not bad:
dressed up, perfumed, a real doll.

164
00:19:11,484 --> 00:19:13,319
I'll come home, Sergio.

165
00:19:13,570 --> 00:19:14,654
Shut up, bitch!

166
00:19:16,448 --> 00:19:19,367
You don't know her? Let me tell you.

167
00:19:19,617 --> 00:19:22,787
She's a bitch. A slut.

168
00:19:23,038 --> 00:19:26,249
A rotten liar, a chicken.

169
00:19:26,708 --> 00:19:27,917
You're pathetic.

170
00:19:29,210 --> 00:19:31,546
And that bitch, your friend Sabine,

171
00:19:31,796 --> 00:19:34,174
always butting in.

172
00:19:34,424 --> 00:19:36,676
What crap did you tell her?

173
00:19:36,926 --> 00:19:40,430
Stop it! I said I'd come home.

174
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:44,184
Sure, you will!
You never had the balls to split.

175
00:19:44,434 --> 00:19:45,435
Listen...

176
00:19:45,894 --> 00:19:47,228
You'll see.

177
00:19:48,897 --> 00:19:52,942
The best day of my life
is when I had you abort.

178
00:19:53,193 --> 00:19:55,445
- Son of a bitch!
- What?

179
00:19:55,779 --> 00:20:00,992
Fuck off, bitch! I'd croak
before I'd have your child.

180
00:20:01,242 --> 00:20:03,703
Scram, you lousy slut!

181
00:20:06,247 --> 00:20:08,291
My God! Are you hurt?

182
00:20:10,418 --> 00:20:12,796
Beat it. What're you doing?

183
00:20:26,893 --> 00:20:29,771
Here. You're bleeding.

184
00:22:52,080 --> 00:22:54,749
We back in Paris?

185
00:22:55,208 --> 00:22:57,252
You never left, sir.

186
00:22:57,502 --> 00:23:01,006
A computer failure.
All planes are grounded.

187
00:23:01,756 --> 00:23:05,802
First class passengers
are being put up at the Hilton.

188
00:23:06,052 --> 00:23:07,595
Duck a l'orange is different!

189
00:23:07,804 --> 00:23:16,229
Shepherd's Pie needs foil containers.
I told you a hundred times.

190
00:23:16,479 --> 00:23:22,068
Did you get Marsha Lipton? Insist!
She's a star in the mid-west.

191
00:23:22,736 --> 00:23:27,073
No, I can't get out
of this goddam country.

192
00:23:27,323 --> 00:23:32,078
Nothing works here:
planes, trains, computers...

193
00:23:32,328 --> 00:23:36,041
Except sleeping pills.
And vacations.

194
00:23:36,291 --> 00:23:42,297
They're overtaxed, unemployed,
at war... And they go on vacation!

195
00:23:43,590 --> 00:23:45,342
I'm spending the night.

196
00:23:45,592 --> 00:23:47,218
Call you tomorrow.

197
00:23:47,469 --> 00:23:50,347
I don't know.
I gotta be in Munich by 3.

198
00:23:50,597 --> 00:23:52,432
No, 3 p.m.

199
00:23:59,773 --> 00:24:01,399
Care for some?

200
00:24:02,692 --> 00:24:04,402
No, thanks.

201
00:24:06,863 --> 00:24:09,407
- A Schoolboy?
- A what?

202
00:24:10,909 --> 00:24:13,495
A chocolate-covered cookie.

203
00:24:13,953 --> 00:24:15,997
No, thanks.

204
00:24:21,795 --> 00:24:24,964
I wanted to thank you.
If it weren't for you...

205
00:24:25,215 --> 00:24:27,342
No, I never should have...

206
00:24:27,592 --> 00:24:29,135
No, honestly.

207
00:24:31,805 --> 00:24:35,809
You're still here, too?
Is it a problem?

208
00:24:36,059 --> 00:24:37,686
I mean, is your trip urgent?

209
00:24:38,853 --> 00:24:40,397
Sure is.

210
00:24:42,315 --> 00:24:48,113
Because for me right now,
an hour more or less...

211
00:24:55,870 --> 00:24:58,957
While you were in the infirmary...

212
00:24:59,207 --> 00:25:03,962
American Airways passengers
for Munich.

213
00:25:04,212 --> 00:25:06,256
Your bus is here.

214
00:25:07,757 --> 00:25:10,218
Goodbye, then.

215
00:25:41,666 --> 00:25:44,419
I have a room at the Hilton.

216
00:25:45,712 --> 00:25:49,841
There must be two beds.
You'd be more comfortable than here.

217
00:25:59,392 --> 00:26:00,685
Forget it.

218
00:26:01,353 --> 00:26:04,022
No, it's very...

219
00:26:04,272 --> 00:26:06,816
nice of you.

220
00:26:08,985 --> 00:26:13,198
True, a real bed would be...

221
00:26:32,967 --> 00:26:34,177
Prefer the window?

222
00:26:34,427 --> 00:26:36,680
This side's fine.

223
00:26:36,930 --> 00:26:39,599
I prefer near the door.

224
00:26:39,849 --> 00:26:41,267
Okay by me.

225
00:26:52,195 --> 00:26:55,448
Smells drive me...
Especially stale smoke.

226
00:26:58,201 --> 00:26:59,661
Do you smoke?

227
00:27:06,584 --> 00:27:08,169
Hungry?

228
00:27:18,847 --> 00:27:20,265
You can take off your coat.

229
00:30:20,028 --> 00:30:22,697
Mister, can you hear me?

230
00:30:23,782 --> 00:30:25,825
Are you okay?

231
00:30:32,540 --> 00:30:34,167
Oh, my God!

232
00:30:34,834 --> 00:30:38,755
I'm fine. I fell asleep, that's all.

233
00:30:39,005 --> 00:30:41,466
- Did I hurt you?
- I was asleep.

234
00:30:41,716 --> 00:30:43,718
- On the floor?
- Yes, on the floor.

235
00:30:44,010 --> 00:30:48,139
Maybe it's those pills.
Did you take more?

236
00:30:48,473 --> 00:30:52,102
I know all about them.
A relative of mine...

237
00:30:52,352 --> 00:30:56,898
It's jet lag. I don't even know
the time. And my pressure...

238
00:30:57,190 --> 00:30:59,609
- Your what?
- My blood pressure.

239
00:30:59,859 --> 00:31:01,486
- Your blood tension!
- That's it.

240
00:31:01,736 --> 00:31:03,363
I haven't had lunch.

241
00:31:03,613 --> 00:31:06,491
Dinner. Me neither.

242
00:31:08,201 --> 00:31:09,494
What do you want?

243
00:31:10,495 --> 00:31:12,539
Nothing, really.

244
00:31:14,874 --> 00:31:17,877
Artichoke salad. Are they fresh?

245
00:31:18,128 --> 00:31:23,299
Then tomato salad and ham.
Is it fresh cut?

246
00:31:25,635 --> 00:31:28,722
A chicken breast, then.
Only drumsticks?

247
00:31:29,597 --> 00:31:32,475
Then ham it is. And French bread.

248
00:31:32,726 --> 00:31:36,229
Not cut, nice and crisp.
How about you?

249
00:31:36,479 --> 00:31:38,940
- Honestly, no.
- Make it for two.

250
00:31:39,399 --> 00:31:41,860
In that case I'd prefer...

251
00:31:42,110 --> 00:31:43,528
Hang on.

252
00:31:46,489 --> 00:31:49,784
"Hare and venison terrine
with pistachios,

253
00:31:50,452 --> 00:31:55,623
"with a pepper mousse and feathered
endives with nuts and Roquefort..."

254
00:31:56,958 --> 00:31:59,794
A hare terrine.
Vinaigrette on the side.

255
00:32:00,045 --> 00:32:02,922
And fruit.
Not a cocktail, just fruit.

256
00:32:04,424 --> 00:32:07,927
In whatever you like.
A basket, fine!

257
00:32:08,595 --> 00:32:11,681
And a Calon-Segur... '96.

258
00:32:14,642 --> 00:32:17,312
Everything's so complicated
in this country.

259
00:32:19,439 --> 00:32:21,483
Aren't you hot?

260
00:32:23,068 --> 00:32:24,402
I was cold earlier.

261
00:32:25,278 --> 00:32:28,365
