606
01:03:48,578 --> 01:03:51,873
He comes up to me: "What's this?"

607
01:03:52,791 --> 01:03:57,504
I was 17,an apprentice,
he didn't trust me with anything.

608
01:03:58,380 --> 01:04:04,386
He made me study bookkeeping,
stuff I hated, even if later...

609
01:04:05,970 --> 01:04:08,473
But I believed in myself.

610
01:04:09,015 --> 01:04:11,393
I said something dumb.

611
01:04:11,643 --> 01:04:13,978
I said, "Dad, it's a miracle!

612
01:04:14,562 --> 01:04:17,816
"It's like penicillin:
due to an error!"

613
01:04:19,025 --> 01:04:21,277
Okay, it was dumb.

614
01:04:23,697 --> 01:04:25,448
He sat down like a customer.

615
01:04:27,367 --> 01:04:29,411
"Go ahead".

616
01:04:30,161 --> 01:04:32,122
I served him.

617
01:04:32,789 --> 01:04:34,624
I was petrified.

618
01:04:38,003 --> 01:04:40,380
He turned to me and said:

619
01:04:41,631 --> 01:04:45,468
"Too much parsley,
not enough garlic."

620
01:04:47,512 --> 01:04:49,514
The jerk!

621
01:04:50,682 --> 01:04:54,853
There was no garlic,
that was the point.

622
01:04:57,397 --> 01:04:59,024
He didn't get it.

623
01:04:59,274 --> 01:05:01,234
My frogs' legs were great!

624
01:05:01,484 --> 01:05:06,865
I'd done something great
and it drove him nuts.

625
